# Logging

The plugin must include logging from the initial development phases.

Separate:

* developer logs
* user logs

Rules:

* do not use `print()` in distributable plugin code
* use logging adapters or QGIS messages instead
* user logs must be understandable and translatable to English and Spanish
* developer logs may contain technical diagnostics
* domain code must not depend on QGIS logging APIs
* isolate logging implementations in `services/`

Minimum flows to log:

* plugin load/unload
* IFC association
* IFC viewer opening
* IFC property reading
* property mapping
* GIS attribute writing
* errors and cancellations
